{{ Infobox Person | name = Ilan Shiloah | native_name = אילן שילוח | native_name_lang = [[Hebrew]] |birth_date = {{Birth year and age|1957}} | birth_place = [[Maoz Haim]] | citizenship = [[Israel]] | education = [[Tel Aviv University]] | spouse = Shira Margalit<ref name=biography>{{cite web|url=https://www.haaretz.co.il/1.1111156|title=דברים שרואים מקאן|access-date=8 February 2018}}</ref> }}
'''Ilan Shiloah''' (also anglicised as '''Shiloach''') is an Israeli businessman. He is the former CEO and chairman of McCann Erickson-Kesher-Barel, Israel's largest advertising firm.<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.haaretz.com/print-edition/business/mccann-kesher-barel-to-fire-5-of-staff-1.16944 | title=McCann-Kesher-Barel to fire 5% of staff | work=Haaretz | date=2003-03-07 | accessdate=6 November 2013 | author=Tsoref, Ayala}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.globes.co.il/en/article-ilan-shiloach-mulls-buying-control-of-channel-10-1001011099|title=Ilan Shiloach mulls buying control of Channel 10|date=17 February 2015|access-date=7 February 2018}}</ref> He is the chairman of The Time; a technology startups investment company. Since 2003, Shiloah has served on the Executive Board of McCann Erickson EMEA.
==Biography== Shiloah was born in [[Maoz Haim]], a Kibbutz in northern Israel. Drafted to the army in 1977, he served in the Special Forces unit [[Sayeret Matkal]]. After completing his service, Shiloah obtained a BA in Economics & Management from [[Tel Aviv University]], where he also achieved an MBA.
In 1995, Shiloah was appointed as the CEO of Kesher-Barel,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.themarker.com/advertising/1.119695 |title=אילן שילוח, מנכ"ל ושותף, מקאן קשר בראל, הוא איש השיווק של החודש - מדיה ופרסום - דה מרקר TheMarker|publisher=www.themarker.com |date=2002-07-11|accessdate=2013-10-26}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.globes.co.il/news/article.aspx?did=833855 |title=התחנה הבאה של אילן שילוח - גלובס |publisher=www.globes.co.il/ |date=2004-09-05|accessdate=2013-10-26}}</ref> which later became McCann Erickson Israel (now part of [[McCann_(company)|McCann WorldGroup]]). Between the years 2009-2011 Shiloah sold his shares in the company to the global McCann Erickson Worldgroup.{{cn|date=February 2018}}
Shiloah was the chairman of [[Matomy Media|Matomy Media Group]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://jewishbusinessnews.com/2013/07/10/matomy-media-group-acquires-the-mobile-affiliate-network-mobaff/ |title=Matomy Media Group acquires the mobile affiliate network MobAff; |publisher=[[Jewish Business News]] |date= |accessdate=2013-10-21}}</ref> a performance-based marketing company, from 2007 to 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.campaignlive.co.uk/article/matomy-group-appoints-former-itv-chief-rupert-howell-non-executive-chairman/1374490|title=Matomy Group appoints former ITV chief Rupert Howell as non-executive chairman|date=25 November 2015|access-date=7 February 2018}}</ref>
Shiloah is the co-founder, major shareholder and chairman of The Time;<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mfa.gov.il/mfa/innovativeisrael/sciencetech/pages/this-is-thetime-for-startups.aspx |title=TheTime for startups 3 Oct 2013|publisher=mfa.gov.il |date= |accessdate=2013-10-17}}</ref> an investment company founded in 2009 focusing on young innovative technology startups in the areas of new media (T.I.M.E). The Time had invested in dozens of start-up companies in the new media market, during the last few years (two examples being MySiteApp and Getonic.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.crunchbase.com/financial-organization/thetime |title=thetime &#124; CrunchBase Profile |publisher=Crunchbase.com |date= |accessdate=2013-10-17}}</ref>)
In 2015, [[Channel_Ten_(Israel)|Channel 10]], of which Shiloah was a minority shareholder, entered financial difficulties and Shiloah attempted to take full control of the broadcaster in return for taking on the existing debts of around NIS 200 million.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.globes.co.il/en/article-regulator-asked-to-approve-shiloah-acquisition-of-channel-10-1001034547|title=Approval sought for Shiloah Channel 10 acquisition|date=7 May 2015|access-date=8 February 2018}}</ref> Shiloah's offer was rejected in favour of an offer by RGE.<ref>[http://www.haaretz.com/israel-news/business/1.658610 ''U.S. Billionaire Set to Save Israel's Debt-strapped Channel 10''], [[Haaretz]], May 28, 2015</ref>
Shiloah is currently chairman of Silenseed, a clinical stage biopharmaceutical company.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://silenseed.com/?page_id=2357|title=Board Of Directors|access-date=8 February 2018}}</ref>
==Personal life==
Shiloah is twice divorced and has four daughters. He is married to Shira Margalit, daughter of [[Dan Margalit]].<ref name=biography/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.haaretz.com/1.5054892|title=Reshet Executive Attacked Outside Home|date=21 May 2009|access-date=8 February 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.haaretz.com/.premium-ceo-of-mccann-erickson-israel-behind-libel-suit-ad-1.5323416|title=CEO of McCann Erickson Israel Behind Ad That Led to Ex-army Spokesmans Libel Suit|date=21 August 2013|access-date=8 February 2018}}</ref> Shiloah lives in Tel Aviv.
