{{Notability|Biographies|date=January 2015}} {{Infobox person | name = Tomi Pierucci | image = Tomi Pierucci.jpg | image_size = | caption = Tomi Pierucci | birth_place = [[Buenos Aires|Buenos Aires, Argentina]]
}} '''Tomi Pierucci''' (born September 6, 1983) is an Argentine entrepreneur. He is the founder of several successful businesses including Little Blue, Big Blue Ideas and [[Bluesmart]].
==Personal life== Tomás Pierucci, better known as Tomi Pierucci, was born in [[Buenos Aires]], Argentina to a family of entrepreneurs.
He studied Marketing at Universidad de Ciencias Empresariales y Sociales and continued his studies at [[IAE Business School]] and [[IESE Business School]]. He started his first company while still in high-school during the middle of Argentina's worst economic crisis.<ref>[https://www.linkedin.com/profile/view?id=189333755&authType=NAME_SEARCH&authToken=RNd2&locale=en_US&trk=tyah2&trkInfo=tarId%3A1419133866242%2Ctas%3Atomi%20pieruc%2Cidx%3A1-1-1] {{dead link|date=January 2015}}</ref><ref name="clarin.com">{{cite web|url=http://www.ieco.clarin.com/economia/Hacer-parar_0_1106889663.html|title=Hacer sin parar|work=Clarin.com|accessdate=20 January 2015}}</ref>
